.TH MYSTIC-TOP 1 "March 2026" "Mystic Monitor 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mystic-top \- interactive process viewer with ML performance degradation prediction
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mystic-top
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mystic-top
provides a dynamic real-time view of a running system, similar to traditional
.IR top (1)
or
.IR htop (1).
However, it connects to the mystic-monitor systemd daemon to provide intelligent, Machine Learning based predictions on potential system slowdowns based on process count, memory, cpu, and disk I/O metrics.

It displays a curated list of system summary information, a prominent status banner predicting degradation, and a list of currently running processes managed by the Linux kernel.
.SH INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
.B mystic-top
accepts single-key commands while running:
.TP
.B q
Quit the program.
.SH FILES
.I /tmp/mystic.sock
.RS
A high-performance Unix Domain Socket where the mystic-monitor systemd background service serves continuous predictions in-memory to all connecting dashboard clients, avoiding disk I/O overhead.
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Mystic Monitor Team
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR top (1),
.IR htop (1)
